stonebridge golf club is a 240-acre golf complex in rome, georgia at the foothills of the appalachian mountains. the stonebridge golf course was designed by arthur l. davis and built in the early 1990s by the city of rome. the golf course is an 18 hole, par 72 course with 6,832 yards of fairway consisting of bermuda grass and creeping bent grass greens. the club features a 5,000-square-foot (460 m2) clubhouse that holds a pro shop and the stonebridge grill. the club also includes a driving range, chipping green, and practice bunker. stonebridge has a resident pga golf professional, adam lyons, and offers private and group classes to all ages and skill levels.